interactions.flavorLineOne:
Your many successes in Calus's Menagerie have more than demonstrated that you are worthy of a new title: Shadow of Earth.

Tread carefully. All of Calus's other Shadows succumbed to inglorious ends.

Via remote mechanism, Calus presents you with your first tribute.

"Take this," he says. "Find a suitable place of honor for it, little Guardian. And then let me see you fill this whole hall until it overflows with the evidence of your golden strength."
As you place your gift at the golden statue's feet, it swivels its head to look at you and opens its mouth. The Emperor laughs, deep and delighted.

Speaking through his robotic double, Calus tells you that Gahlran's so-called Crown of Sorrow had a very peculiar effect on the Leviathan—it briefly split the seams of reality, allowing access to an altered plane of reality that Calus believes you're quite familiar with.

Calus's men ventured in and found the frame of a cursed gun. Since then, the gun's incorporeal essence has tormented the Leviathan's upper decks and eluded Calus's grasp.

Perhaps you'll have better luck than the Cabal.

Calus has a deep and abiding admiration for your tenacity and endurance. As a small token of his affection, he has built this Tribute Hall for you to fill with trophies.

Of course, you'll have to earn those trophies…
